Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -eux

    # Update package lists and install python3-pip so we can add pytest
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3-pip

    # Install pytest for the automated grader
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial exercise state expected by the tests
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # 1. Create the user's home and the project directory with one file.
    mkdir -p /home/user/project

    # Add a non-empty sample file so the backup has something to pack.
    echo "Sample content for the monitoring-platform backup proof-of-concept." \
        > /home/user/project/sample.txt

    # 2. Ensure permissions allow the non-root runtime user to work there.
    #    The exact UID/GID at runtime is unknown, so make the directory
    #    universally writable while keeping reasonable read/execute bits.
    chmod 0777 /home/user
    chmod -R a+rX /home/user/project
    # (Do NOT create /home/user/backup here; it must be absent initially.)

    # Clean up apt caches to keep the image small
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author backup-proof-of-concept-preparer
    Description "Container providing initial state for backup PoC exercise"

%help
This Apptainer image contains:
  • /home/user/project      with a sample.txt file
  • NO /home/user/backup    directory yet (must be created by the learner)

Pytest is installed so the automated grader can run its tests.